```python
import pandas as pd

df = pd.DataFrame({
    "sample": ["S1","S2","S3","S4","S5","S6","S7","S8"],
    "titer":  [2.1, 2.3, 2.2, 2.4, 2.1, 2.2, 3.0, 1.5]
})
display(df)
```

```python
df['z_score'] = (df['titer']-df['titer'].mean())/df['titer'].std(ddof=0)
```

```python
import numpy as np
df['is_outlier'] = df['z_score'].abs()>=2.0
outlier_samples = df[df['is_outlier']==True]['sample'].to_list()
mean_all = df['titer'].mean()
mean_no_outlier = df[df['is_outlier']==False]['titer'].mean()
display(df, outlier_samples, mean_all, mean_no_outlier)
```

```python
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(7,4))
df_copy = df.copy()
df_copy = df_copy.sort_values(by='sample')
color = df_copy['is_outlier'].map({True: 'red', False: 'blue'})
ax.scatter(df_copy['sample'], df_copy['titer'], marker ='o', color = color)
xmin, xmax = ax.get_xlim()
ax.axhline(mean_all, linestyle='--', color = 'gray', linewidth=2)
ax.axhline(mean_no_outlier, linestyle='-', color = 'black', linewidth=2)
ax.set_title("Titer Distribution with Outliers")
ax.set_xlabel('Sample')
ax.set_ylabel('Titer')
ax.grid(False)
```
